The House Committee on Ways and Means offers the following substitute to HB 66:
A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Chapter 5C of Title 48 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to title
2 ad valorem tax on motor vehicles, so as to provide for an alternative method for payment of
3 such ad valorem tax for certain modified rental vehicles; to provide for definitions; to provide
4 for related matters; to repeal conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
5 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
6 SECTION 1.
7 Chapter 5C of Title 48 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to title ad valorem
8 tax on motor vehicles, is amended in subsection (d) of Code Section 48-5C-1, relating to
9 alternative ad valorem taxation of motor vehicles and title ad valorem tax fee, by repealing
10 paragraph (7.1) and adding a new paragraph to read as follows:
11 "(19)(A) As used in this paragraph, the term:
12 (i) 'For-hire charter bus or motor coach' means a motor vehicle designed for carrying
13 more than 15 passengers and used for the transportation of persons for compensation.
14 (ii) 'Special modified rental vehicle' means a motor vehicle that has been significantly
15 modified at a manufacturing facility in this state, provided that:
16 (I) Such manufacturing facility is operated by the owner of such motor vehicle;
