17 (II) Such owner primarily uses such motor vehicle by renting or leasing it without
18 a driver to businesses; and
19 (III) Such rental or lease transactions are subject to Georgia state and local sales
20 and use taxes.
21 (B) In the case of for-hire charter buses or motor coaches or special modified rental
22 vehicles, the person applying for a certificate of title shall be required to pay title ad
23 valorem tax fees in the amount of 50 percent of the amount which would otherwise be
24 due and payable under this subsection at the time of filing the application for a
25 certificate of title, and the remaining 50 percent shall be paid within 12 months
26 following the filing of such application."
27 SECTION 2.
28 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
